No.55/4/CF-64 (i)
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
IMMED IATE
New Delhi, the 2nd July 1964.
The undersigned is directed to state that, with effect
from the forenoon of July 2, 1964,
(i) Shri Satya Narayan Sinha, Minister of Communications
and Parliamentary Affairs, relinquished his temporary
charge of the Ministry of Information & Broadcasting;
and
(ii) Shrimati Indira Gandhi assumed the office of Minister
of Information & Broadcasting.
(D.P. Chopra)
for Cabinet Secretary.
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Principal Private Secretary to the
Prime Minister/the Private Secretary to the Prime Minister, for
information,
*0* I'd

Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/the
Private Secretary to the Vice-President, for information.
(D.P. Chopra)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
Copy forworded to all Secretaries/Special Secretaries/
Additional Secretaries to the Government of India/Chairman,
Railway Board/Secretary, Election Comnission, for information.
Copy forwarded to all linistries of the Government of
India/Department of Parliamentay Affairs/Planning Commission/
Department of Atomic Energy/Prime Minister's Secretariat/Lok
Sabha Secretariat/Rajya Sabha Secretariat, for information.
(D.P. Chopra)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
